               <head>Tahẕīb al-Akhlāq</head>
               <msContents class="https://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85068451.html https://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2008104964">
                  <summary>A Persian didactic treatise by an unnamed author on practical morality,
                     titled <title>Tahẕīb al-Akhlāq</title>. The work has three sections (<hi
                        rend="italic">bāb</hi>) dedicated to the three components of 'practical
                     wisdom' (<hi rend="italic">ḥikmat-i ʿamalī</hi>). This manuscript seems to be
                     the only listed copy. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_909-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23477">Tahẕīb al-Akhlāq</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">تهذیب الاخلاق</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">اخلاق مهذبۀ اهل کمال که لایق اتباع و انتخاب تواند بود
                        حمد حضرت مبدع قدیمست</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">پیوسته بر ملازمت سیرت عدل و التزام طریق | حق مواظبت کن
                        تا نیکبخت دوجهانی | باشی و الله الموفق الساکن و الماشی والسلام</explicit>
                     <colophon>(ff. 109v and 110r) Completed in Shaʿbān 1094 (July/August 1683) in
                        Akbarabad. </colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
